Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language understanding and dialogue management in chatbots. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of Deep Reinforcement Learning for policy learning in chatbots. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper introduces a transfer learning method to improve the performance of chatbots. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) could be a possible category as the paper deals with the development of chatbot systems. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also possible as the paper discusses the success rate of chatbots in achieving user goals, which is a key aspect of user experience.
